---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { Container } from '../../components/layout/Container';
import { Section } from '../../components/layout/Section';
import { Heading } from '../../components/ui/Heading';
import { Badge } from '../../components/ui/Badge';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="7 Keyword Strategies That Actually Drive Profit (Not Just Traffic)"
  description="Master profitable keyword selection for Google Ads. Stop wasting budget on low-intent searches and focus on keywords that convert."
>
  <Section background="white" spacing="lg">
    <Container size="lg">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <Badge variant="info" size="md" className="mb-6">Tactics</Badge>
        <Heading as="h1" size="5xl" className="mb-6">
          7 Keyword Strategies That Actually Drive Profit
        </Heading>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
          The difference between "cheap furniture" and "buy handcrafted leather sofa online" is thousands in revenue. Master profitable keyword selection.
        </p>

        <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
          <p>
            Most Google Ads accounts waste 30-40% of their budget on keywords that will never convert. Why? Because they focus on volume instead of intent.
          </p>

          <p>
            This guide shows you exactly how to identify high-profit keywords and eliminate the ones burning your cash.
          </p>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            1. Buyer Intent Modifiers
          </Heading>

          <p>
            Add these modifiers to your keywords to target people ready to buy:
          </p>

          <div class="bg-emerald-50 border-l-4 border-emerald-500 p-6 my-6">
            <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-900 mb-2">High-Intent Modifiers:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-emerald-800">
              <li>• "buy" (e.g., "buy standing desk")</li>
              <li>• "order" (e.g., "order office chairs online")</li>
              <li>• "price" / "cost" (e.g., "ergonomic chair price")</li>
              <li>• "near me" (e.g., "furniture store near me")</li>
              <li>• "best" (e.g., "best CRM software")</li>
              <li>• "review" (e.g., "HubSpot review")</li>
              <li>• "vs" / "comparison" (e.g., "Shopify vs WooCommerce")</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <p class="font-semibold text-lg">
            Real Example: An e-commerce client added "buy" modifiers to their top 50 keywords. CPA dropped 43% while maintaining volume.
          </p>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            2. Negative Keyword Ruthlessness
          </Heading>

          <p>
            Your negative keyword list is more important than your target keyword list. Here's what to block immediately:
          </p>

          <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-6 my-6">
            <p class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">Universal Negative Keywords:</p>
            <ul class="space-y-1 text-red-800 font-mono text-sm">
              <li>• free, cheap, discount, sale, clearance</li>
              <li>• diy, how to, tutorial, guide (unless you sell courses)</li>
              <li>• jobs, careers, hiring, resume</li>
              <li>• used, refurbished, second hand</li>
              <li>• porn, xxx, adult (add brand protection)</li>
              <li>• wiki, wikipedia, definition</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            3. The Long-Tail Goldmine
          </Heading>

          <p>
            Long-tail keywords (4+ words) have:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>70% lower CPCs</li>
            <li>2.5x higher conversion rates</li>
            <li>Better ROI than broad terms</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg my-6">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-2">Example Comparison:</p>
            <table class="min-w-full text-sm">
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-blue-200">
                  <th class="text-left py-2">Keyword Type</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-2">CPC</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-2">Conv Rate</th>
                  <th class="text-left py-2">CPA</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr class="border-b border-blue-100">
                  <td class="py-2">"furniture"</td>
                  <td class="py-2">$3.20</td>
                  <td class="py-2">0.8%</td>
                  <td class="py-2">$400</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-blue-100">
                  <td class="py-2">"office furniture"</td>
                  <td class="py-2">$2.10</td>
                  <td class="py-2">1.5%</td>
                  <td class="py-2">$140</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="py-2 font-semibold">"buy ergonomic office chair Los Angeles"</td>
                  <td class="py-2 font-semibold">$1.20</td>
                  <td class="py-2 font-semibold">4.2%</td>
                  <td class="py-2 font-semibold text-emerald-600">$29</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            4. Competitor Brand Targeting
          </Heading>

          <p>
            Bidding on competitor brand names can be incredibly profitable IF done right:
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-4 my-6">
            <div class="border-l-4 border-emerald-500 pl-4">
              <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-900">✓ DO bid on competitors if:</p>
              <ul class="text-emerald-800 text-sm mt-2">
                <li>• You offer a better price/value</li>
                <li>• They have poor reviews</li>
                <li>• You have a unique differentiator</li>
                <li>• Their product is being discontinued</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
              <p class="font-semibold text-red-900">✗ DON'T bid on competitors if:</p>
              <ul class="text-red-800 text-sm mt-2">
                <li>• You can't match their offer</li>
                <li>• They have strong brand loyalty</li>
                <li>• Your budget is limited (focus on your own brand first)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            5. Search Term Mining
          </Heading>

          <p>
            Your search terms report is a goldmine. Review it weekly and:
          </p>

          <ol class="space-y-3">
            <li>
              <strong>Add high-performers as exact match keywords</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">If a search term converts at 2x your account average, add it as an exact match keyword with higher bids.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Negative match the garbage</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Anything with 50+ clicks and 0 conversions? Negative keyword immediately.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Identify patterns</strong>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Notice "color" shows up a lot? Create color-specific ad groups.</p>
            </li>
          </ol>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            6. Match Type Strategy
          </Heading>

          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg my-6">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-4">Our Proven Match Type Framework:</p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Exact Match (60% of budget)</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Your proven converters. Max bids. Full control.</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-600">Phrase Match (30% of budget)</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Discovery and expansion. Mine for new exact match keywords.</p>
              </div>

              <div>
                <p class="font-semibold text-yellow-600">Broad Match (10% of budget, if at all)</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">Only use with Smart Bidding and heavy negative keyword lists. High risk.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            7. Profit-Based Keyword Segmentation
          </Heading>

          <p>
            Not all keywords deserve the same bid. Segment by profit margin:
          </p>

          <div class="bg-emerald-50 border-2 border-emerald-500 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
            <p class="font-semibold text-emerald-900 mb-3">Campaign Structure Example:</p>

            <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
              <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
                <p class="font-semibold">Campaign: High-Margin Products (50%+ margin)</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Target ROAS: 300% | Max CPC: $15</p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
                <p class="font-semibold">Campaign: Medium-Margin Products (30-50% margin)</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Target ROAS: 400% | Max CPC: $8</p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
                <p class="font-semibold">Campaign: Low-Margin Products (10-30% margin)</p>
                <p class="text-gray-600">Target ROAS: 600% | Max CPC: $3</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <Heading as="h2" size="3xl" className="mb-4 mt-12">
            Action Plan
          </Heading>

          <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
            <p class="font-semibold mb-4">This Week:</p>
            <ol class="space-y-2">
              <li>1. Export your search terms report (last 90 days)</li>
              <li>2. Add 50+ negative keywords</li>
              <li>3. Identify your top 10 converting search terms → add as exact match</li>
              <li>4. Segment campaigns by profit margin</li>
              <li>5. Add buyer intent modifiers to your top 20 keywords</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <p class="font-semibold text-lg mt-12">
            Want us to audit your keyword strategy? <a href="/free-analysis" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Get a free profit analysis</a> and we'll show you exactly which keywords are profitable and which are burning cash.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
